The growing power of Hamas, which openly proclaims its strategy of increasing acts of terrorism and destroy Israel, does that strengthen this trend.
We can say the same of Syria, whose radical Government turns to a dangerously adventurous militancy.
Sharon could decide on partial withdrawals and dismantling of settlements in the West Bank.
But it is now widely accepted that such changes are a reaction to bleak prospects for real progress towards peace.
Cling to territories to make a bargain issues has much less sense if there's nobody with that bargain.
Israel will continue instead to treat as a priority its own security, strengthening its defences against terrorism and consolidating his control over relatively small portions of the West Bank that it intends to claim as its share of a possible diplomatic agreement.
