Global flows of foreign direct investment (FDI) have exploded during the past twenty years, from $ 40 billion in the early 1980s to $ 900 billion last year.
The cumulative stock of FDI reached nearly 10 trillion, making it the most important mechanism of delivery of goods and services to foreign markets: sales by foreign affiliates total roughly 19 trillion, compared to world exports of $ 11 trillion.
