The Minister of the Interior wants that driver who has had more than three administrative sanctions for drink, has to install in his vehicle a system that prevents from starting the vehicle in a State of drunkenness, or if it does not blow.
The initiative was already announced last June and it now appears in the report of the Minister of State in which this initiative is seen as a pilot project which will last one year.
Its aim is the reintegration of the driver by offering road rehabilitation courses.
