According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of motorists arrested for driving more than once in a State of drunkenness, takes over the car.
The alcolock avoid this because it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures alcohol in the breath and prevents from start the vehicle if the driver is blowing not before; or when the alcohol level of the driver is higher than permitted.
Its cost is greater than 1,000 euros and is the responsibility of the driver.
In this regard, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with this device reduced up to 65% of the offences in the first year of installation.
And in Spain it is estimated that it could save the lives of 115 people every year.
This measure is only to administrative penalties for two reasons: to deal with these behaviors before they turn into criminal offences.
And facilitate its implementation, since the legal reform can be made through ordinary channels but, however, the reform made by criminal requires a reform of the organic law.
The device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any form commercial, although some industrial vehicles and service already has one on an experimental basis.
Precisely tomorrow, the Congress of deputies will vote an initiative of the Spanish Socialist Party which proposes to install this system on school buses as has been done in France.
