A few children speak during the night.
I do not refer to those who are waking up very awake telling something that happened the day of before, but children who speak during their sleep.
The first time that this happens it may surprise you, but in reality it has no importance.
It is a benign alteration of sleep called somniloquy.
It is quite common, especially in children and adolescents.
It is sure that there is more than one who speaks during the night.
This phenomenon can occur very sporadically (once in life for example associated with an episode of high fever), or on a more regular basis (every day, once a week, once a month...), the day after the child will remember nothing.
There is no single cause that determines its appearance.
They are often related to other alterations in sleep as nightmares, night terrors, night enuresis (bedwetting do) or sleepwalking, but this is not always the case.
As said before, they can also be associated with very high fevers, in situations of stress or excitement.
Anyway it is a little-studied phenomenon.
The intensity with which it occurs is also highly variable.
It may be that he speaks with a small quiet voice, with isolated words, whispers or shouts, tears, long speeches...
Where the somniloquy becomes busy, it would be wise to observe the child and consult a specialist to verify if there is a problem that causes a lot of anxiety and to obtain an explanation to this problem.
We said that it is a benign alteration, it is why it has no treatment, unless it is linked to another alteration of sleep which can be treated (for example, if it is related to a sleep apnea or stress).
What we can do is to take into account a number of very simple preventive measures such as:
Try not to excite the child before going to sleep.
Therefore seek quiet games and avoid programs or dramas that are more or less violent.
With very nervous children difficult to relax, and relaxation techniques can be used to help calm down internally.
This will allow the child to have a more peaceful sleep.
As soon as the somniloquies appear try to stay calm.
Remember they are harmless for the child and the next day he no longer what remembered happened.
