Michelin and Fesvial, sets for the wearing of helmets.
The manufacturer of Michelin tyres, in collaboration with the Spanish Foundation for road safety (Fesvial), has launched a campaign to encourage the headset port, mainly among younger riders, as reported today the two structures.
This initiative is designed to raise awareness of the importance of the helmet, since it is the only element of protection to "avoid injuries to the head, or even death, accident on two wheels.
Michelin indicated that this campaign was in line with its commitment to road safety, which "goes to-beyond of the design and manufacture of still safer products" and stated that it was contributing to this objective by other actions in educational and informative character.
This new campaign of encouragement of the helmet on two wheels, under the motto "To be or not to be", will include an initial phase during which posters will be distributed in over 500 garages for motorcycles, in order to ensure the widest possible dissemination.
